cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Protocol Implementation Performance Evaluation Under Varying Bandwidth
  and File Size Constraints
abstract: This dataset evaluates QUIC protocol implementations across multiple configurations,
  measuring performance metrics such as goodput, latency, and success rates under
  controlled bandwidth limits and file sizes. Server and client workloads were executed
  on two nodes, capturing logs, energy usage, and cryptographic handshake data. Evaluation
  scripts aggregate results, generating statistical summaries, boxplots, and TSV files
  to compare implementation behavior. Artifacts include per-run server/client logs,
  compiled binaries, and metrics from 72 repetitions across configurations.
